# State & Data-Fetching Conventions

## State Ownership

| State type | Tool |
|---|---|
| Server/async data | TanStack Query |
| Form state | React Hook Form + zod schema |
| Local UI state | `useState` / `useReducer` in feature hook |
| Global app state | Avoid; prefer co-location |

## TanStack Query Rules

- Query keys defined in `data/` layer (co-locate with fetcher)
- Mutations invalidate only the relevant query keys
- Do not call `useQuery` / `useMutation` directly in `pages/` or `components/` — wrap in feature hooks

## Anti-Patterns

❌ Duplicate state from the same server source in multiple places  
❌ Fetching data inside `components/` directly  
❌ Managing server state with `useState` + `useEffect` manually  
❌ Putting query keys as inline strings — define as constants
